Class.Name: NSDictionary
Class.Description: A static collection of objects associated with unique keys.

InstanceMethods.Name: init
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated dictionary.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithObjects:forKeys:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated dictionary with key-value pairs constructed from the provided arrays of keys and objects.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithObjects:forKeys:count:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated dictionary with the specified number of key-value pairs constructed from the provided C arrays of keys and objects.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithObjectsAndKeys:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated dictionary with entries constructed from the specified set of values and keys.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithDictionary:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated dictionary by placing in it the keys and values contained in another given dictionary.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithDictionary:copyItems:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated dictionary using the objects contained in another given dictionary.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfURL:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated dictionary using the keys and values found at a given URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfURL:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated dictionary using the keys and values found at a given URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfFile:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated dictionary using the keys and values found in a file at a given path.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithCoder:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates a dictionary initialized from data in the provided unarchiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: isEqualToDictionary:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the contents of the receiving dictionary are equal to the contents of another given dictionary.

InstanceMethods.Name: allKeysForObject:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new array containing the keys corresponding to all occurrences of a given object in the dictionary.

InstanceMethods.Name: valueForKey:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the value associated with a given key.

InstanceMethods.Name: getObjects:andKeys:count:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns by reference C arrays of the keys and values in the dictionary.

InstanceMethods.Name: getObjects:andKeys:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns by reference C arrays of the keys and values in the dictionary.

InstanceMethods.Name: objectsForKeys:notFoundMarker:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns as a static array the set of objects from the dictionary that corresponds to the specified keys.

InstanceMethods.Name: objectForKey:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the value associated with a given key.

InstanceMethods.Name: objectForKeyedSubscript:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the value associated with a given key.

InstanceMethods.Name: keyEnumerator
InstanceMethods.Description: Provides an enumerator to access the keys in the dictionary.

InstanceMethods.Name: objectEnumerator
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an enumerator object that lets you access each value in the dictionary.

InstanceMethods.Name: enumerateKeysAndObjectsUsingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Applies a given block object to the entries of the dictionary.

InstanceMethods.Name: enumerateKeysAndObjectsWithOptions:usingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Applies a given block object to the entries of the dictionary, with options specifying how the enumeration is performed.

InstanceMethods.Name: countByEnumeratingWithState:objects:count:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns by reference a C array of objects over which the sender should iterate.

InstanceMethods.Name: keysSortedByValueUsingSelector:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array of the dictionary’s keys, in the order they would be in if the dictionary were sorted by its values.

InstanceMethods.Name: keysSortedByValueUsingComparator:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array of the dictionary’s keys, in the order they would be in if the dictionary were sorted by its values using a given comparator block.

InstanceMethods.Name: keysSortedByValueWithOptions:usingComparator:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array of the dictionary’s keys, in the order they would be in if the dictionary were sorted by its values using a given comparator block and a specified set of options.

InstanceMethods.Name: keysOfEntriesPassingTest:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the set of keys whose corresponding value satisfies a constraint described by a block object.

InstanceMethods.Name: keysOfEntriesWithOptions:passingTest:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the set of keys whose corresponding value satisfies a constraint described by a block object.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToURL:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes a property list representation of the contents of the dictionary to a given URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToURL:atomically:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes a property list representation of the contents of the dictionary to a given URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToFile:atomically:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes a property list representation of the contents of the dictionary to a given path.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileSize
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the file’s size, in bytes.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileType
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the file type.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileCreationDate
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the file’s creation date.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileModificationDate
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns file’s modification date.

InstanceMethods.Name: filePosixPermissions
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the file’s POSIX permissions.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileOwnerAccountID
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the file’s owner account ID.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileOwnerAccountName
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the file’s owner account name.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileGroupOwnerAccountID
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns file’s group owner account ID.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileGroupOwnerAccountName
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the file’s group owner account name.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileExtensionHidden
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the file hides its extension.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileIsImmutable
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the file is immutable.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileIsAppendOnly
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the file is append only.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileSystemFileNumber
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the filesystem file number.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileSystemNumber
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the filesystem number.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileHFSTypeCode
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns file’s HFS type code.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileHFSCreatorCode
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the file’s HFS creator code.

InstanceMethods.Name: descriptionWithLocale:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a string object that represents the contents of the dictionary, formatted as a property list.

InstanceMethods.Name: descriptionWithLocale:indent:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a string object that represents the contents of the dictionary, formatted as a property list.

InstanceProperties.Name: count
InstanceProperties.Description: The number of entries in the dictionary.

InstanceProperties.Name: allKeys
InstanceProperties.Description: A new array containing the dictionary’s keys, or an empty array if the dictionary has no entries.

InstanceProperties.Name: allValues
InstanceProperties.Description: A new array containing the dictionary’s values, or an empty array if the dictionary has no entries.

InstanceProperties.Name: description
InstanceProperties.Description: A string that represents the contents of the dictionary, formatted as a property list.

InstanceProperties.Name: descriptionInStringsFileFormat
InstanceProperties.Description: A string that represents the contents of the dictionary, formatted in .strings file format.

TypeMethods.Name: dictionaryWithObjects:forKeys:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates a dictionary containing entries constructed from the contents of an array of keys and an array of values.

TypeMethods.Name: dictionaryWithObjects:forKeys:count:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates a dictionary containing a specified number of objects from a C array.

TypeMethods.Name: dictionaryWithObjectsAndKeys:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates a dictionary containing entries constructed from the specified set of values and keys.

TypeMethods.Name: dictionaryWithObject:forKey:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates a dictionary containing a given key and value.

TypeMethods.Name: dictionaryWithDictionary:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates a dictionary containing the keys and values from another given dictionary.

TypeMethods.Name: dictionaryWithContentsOfURL:error:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates a dictionary using the keys and values found in a resource specified by a given URL.

TypeMethods.Name: dictionaryWithContentsOfURL:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates a dictionary using the keys and values found in a resource specified by a given URL.

TypeMethods.Name: dictionaryWithContentsOfFile:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates a dictionary using the keys and values found in a file specified by a given path.

TypeMethods.Name: sharedKeySetForKeys:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates a shared key set object for the specified keys.
